Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Standish","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name from Standish (Lancashire, now part of Greater Manchester), from Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>edisc</i> ‘enclosure, enclosed park’. Standish (Gloucestershire) does not appear to have contributed towards the surname.","History: Myles Standish (<i>c.</i> 1584–1656) was a soldier of fortune, from 1620 captain of the <i>Mayflower</i> Pilgrims at Plymouth Colony. Little is known of his origins and early life, but in his will he claimed to be descended from a leading Catholic family, the Standishes of Standish, Lancashire, England. He also claimed to have been deprived of his inheritance, a claim not confirmed."],"variants":[{"name":"Standage","meanings":["English:","probably a variant of   Standish  .","in Leicestershire and Buckinghamshire, the name may alternatively be from Stanedge Grange in Hartington Nether Quarter or Stanage End in Outseats (both Derbyshire); but evidence is needed for this. The placenames derive from Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>ecg</i> ‘edge, escarpment’."]}]},{"name":"Leising","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Armin, Erwin, Otto.","English: from an Old Norse personal name or nickname, <i>Leysingi</i>, from <i>leysingi</i> ‘freedman’. Compare   Lazenby  .","South German: habitational name from Leising in Bavaria, Styria (Austria), or from Leissing in Franconia."],"variants":[{"name":"Leisinger","meanings":["South German: habitational name for someone from Leising (see   Leising  )."]},{"name":"Lazenby","meanings":["English (northern): habitational name from either of the places called Lazenby in North Yorkshire (one near Northallerton and another near Ormesby), or Lazonby in Cumbria, all of which are named in Old Norse as ‘freedman's farm’, or ‘Freedmen's farm’, from <i>leysingi</i> ‘freedman’ (also used as a nickname and personal name; see   Leising  ) + <i>bý</i> ‘farm, settlement’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Leising de Standish was born in 1135, in Standish, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Radulphus De Standish, was 20 and his mother, Juliana, was 20. He had at least 2 sons with Edith Spileman. He died in 1205, in Standish, Lancashire, England, at the age of 70, and was buried in Standish, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1135–1205":"1135–1205","–1246":"–1246","1142–1160":"1142–1160","1159–Male":"1159–Surnud","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1115–1175":"1115–1175","1115–Female":"1115–Surnud","1206":"1206","1205":"1205","1115":"1115","1159":"1159","1246":"1246","1135":"1135","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","aproximadamente 1159":"umbes 1159","1160":"1160","1219":"1219","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1135–1205":"1135–1205","–1246":"–1246","1142–1160":"1142–1160","1159–Male":"1159–Kuollut","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1115–1175":"1115–1175","1115–Female":"1115–Kuollut","1206":"1206","1205":"1205","1115":"1115","1159":"1159","1246":"1246","1135":"1135","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","aproximadamente 1159":"noin 1159","1160":"1160","1219":"1219","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1135–1205":"1135–1205","–1246":"–1246","1142–1160":"1142–1160","1159–Male":"1159–Décédé","1160–1219":"1160–1219","1115–11